Package com.amazonaws.services.iot.model

Class UpdateAccountAuditConfigurationRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.amazonaws.AmazonWebServiceRequest
      • com.amazonaws.services.iot.model.UpdateAccountAuditConfigurationRequest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
    public class UpdateAccountAuditConfigurationRequest
extends AmazonWebServiceRequest
implements java.io.Serializable

    Configures or reconfigures the Device Defender audit settings for this account. Settings include how audit notifications are sent and which audit checks are enabled or disabled.

    Requires permission to access the UpdateAccountAuditConfiguration action.

      • getAuditCheckConfigurations

        public java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​AuditCheckConfiguration> getAuditCheckConfigurations()

        Specifies which audit checks are enabled and disabled for this account. Use DescribeAccountAuditConfiguration to see the list of all checks, including those that are currently enabled.

        Some data collection might start immediately when certain checks are enabled. When a check is disabled, any data collected so far in relation to the check is deleted.

        You cannot disable a check if it's used by any scheduled audit. You must first delete the check from the scheduled audit or delete the scheduled audit itself.

        On the first call to UpdateAccountAuditConfiguration, this parameter is required and must specify at least one enabled check.

        Returns:
